description: A six-month old puppy named Stormy is expected to make a full recovery after it was stabbed in the head by a neighbor.

title: Aussie man living in London is fleeced more than $330,000 in overseas scam
description: Claiming to be the vice president for the Bank of America, Rajesh Ghedia was able to scam out of more than $330,000 from Wayne Johncock set aside for his education company.

title: Queensland dog owner Rose fined $350 after moving to NSW and forgetting to cancel pet's registration
description: A single mum has been caught out by the 'fine print' of her dog registration and slugged a huge fine when she moved from Queensland to New South Wales. Now she's warning other dog owners.

title: Judge who freed Rubin 'Hurricane' Carter dies aged 94: H. Lee Sarokin also slammed tobacco industry
description: The federal judge who freed Rubin 'Hurricane' Carter after he was convicted of triple murder has died at the age of 94.

title: 'I'm being indicted for you' Trump tells his MAGA faithful
description: Former President Donald Trump rolled out a possible new campaign slogan Saturday night at the Faith & Freedom Coalition conference in Washington, D.C.: 'I'm being indicted for you.'

title: England's best pub gardens revealed, from a hipster London watering hole to the UK's only beach bar
description: Hop to it! It's that time of year when everybody is scrambling to find the perfect beer garden with good drinks on tap, hearty pub grub, and gorgeous views as an added bonus.

title: Michigan man in disbelief after he finds winning lottery ticket worth $200,000 stuffed in his wallet
description: Yandiel Cruz-Chavez from Michigan purchased a Fantasy 5 lottery ticket for a mere $1, winning the $200,000 jackpot which he only discovered one month later after he rediscovered his ticket.

title: Youngest person ever to explore Titanic wreck says he would NEVER have stepped foot on the Titan
description: The youngest person ever to explore the Titanic wreck has revealed he would never have stepped foot on the Titan.

title: Car insurance rates soar by up to FORTY percent - how hard has YOUR state been hit by price hikes?
description: The cost of living in the United States has risen sharply over the past year and car insurance is no different as some rates have risen by as much as 40 percent.

title: Governor Andrew Bailey blamed for crippling rise in mortgage bills
description: Bank of England Governor Andrew Bailey has been accused by Tory MPs of 'going for woke' rather than concentrating on his 'day job' of controlling inflation.

title: Fox News analyst Gianno Caldwell calls on the FBI to investigate his youngest brother's murder
description: Fox News analyst Gianno Caldwell has called upon the FBI to investigate his brother's murder after claiming Chicago Police has failed his family.

title: Nationals leader David Littleproud could be dumped - Barnaby Joyce or Keith Pitt tipped for job
description: National Party leader David Littleproud tried on Sunday morning to hose down speculation he could soon face a challenge for his position, with a serial candidate in line to replace him.

title: Shaun Bailey admits he WAS in the same building as lockdown-breaking boozy Xmas party
description: Evidence has come to light that Lord Bailey remained in the building while his staff were dancing - timestamps from a film of his team dancing and his BBC News appearance recorded in another room.

title: 'We're coming for your children': Topless activists and drag queens spark outrage at NYC Pride
description: Activists and drag queens taking part in a march through Manhattan on Friday were heard chanting: 'We're here, we're queer, we're coming for your children.' The chant sparked anger.

title: Kirsty Armstrong: family of young woman killed in crash in Molong NSW speak out
description: The parents of a young mother killed after allegedly being driven off the road by her estranged husband have lashed domestic violence services for 'failing' their daughter.

title: Glastonbury sings for Lewis Capaldi as singer struggles with Tourette's
description: The singer, 26, who has Tourette's syndrome, cancelled all work commitments earlier this month to 'rest and recover' ahead of the music festival.

title: Why 'Tall Paul' is the only aide the King trusts to sort through his mother's private diaries
description: Choosing which papers are private is a job that requires discretion, given they may contain the late Queen's innermost thoughts. Which is why the King has given the task to  retired footman 'Tall Paul'.

title: Wealthy US entrepreneur bankrolling Just Stop Oil turns on 'unproductive' climate mob
description: Trevor Neilson co-founded the Climate Emergency Fund (CEF), a group that bankrolled Extinction Rebellion and JSO, but resigned his position in 2021 and described their methods as 'unproductive'.

title: Jeremy Hunt tells banks to raise rates for savers to offset the pain caused by mortgage bills
description: Writing in today's Mail on Sunday, Mr Hunt said he had made it clear to the companies 'that on the other side of the coin we expect savers to be getting a fair deal'.

title: Empty seats and heckled off stage. How SNP leader Humza Yousaf's independence rally ended in farce
description: Humza Yousaf's flagship independence convention descended into farce yesterday after the SNP leader was heckled off stage by a furious party member during his speech.

title: Most of the rate chiefs from the Bank of England inflicting pain on homeowners do not have mortgages
description: Analysis of Land Registry data shows that seven out of nine members of the Monetary Policy Committee (MPC), which sets the base rate, do not have home loans for their UK properties.

title: Trans activist left bloodied after clashes with far-right protesters outside a drag queen event
description: The trans group claimed that yesterday morning they were attacked while standing outside the Magical Storytelling time event for children at the Honor Oak pub in Lewisham, South London.

title: King Charles and Queen Camilla wave to fans as they arrive for the final day of Royal Ascot
description: After arriving at the Berkshire racecourse in a horse-drawn carriage, the newly-crowned monarch, 74, made his way up to the Royal box with his wife Queen Camilla.

title: Home Secretary Suella Braverman locked in row with Mark Zuckerberg over child abuse fear
description: The Home Secretary said she was writing to Mark Zuckerberg to argue that his plans for end-to-end encryption would restrict the ability of the authorities to detect instances of child grooming.

title: Britons feel least valued in their late 50s - but their self-worth recovers as they get older
description: Thirty-nine per cent in their late 50s say they feel insignificant - more than in any other age group. But for those in their 70s, that figure drops to just 15 per cent.

title: Now NHS tells Scottish mums: Please DON'T use gas and air in childbirth … it's bad for the planet
description: The Scottish Government has written to all health boards with an NHS plan which suggests women should be encouraged not to use Entonox for the good of the planet.

title: White undercover NYPD detective sues city for discrimination
description: A white NYPD officer is taking legal action against the force claiming that his colleagues of color discriminated against him because of his race.

title: Water company enforcing hosepipe ban from midnight leaks 92m litres of water a day
description: A water company enforcing a hosepipe ban from midnight tonight leaks enough water to fill Wembley Stadium 33 times a year - but is now blaming customers for shortages.

title: Did you think it was scorching at Glasto? There are another FIVE heatwaves on the way...
description: Revellers at Glastonbury, including Taron Egerton and Lily James, have been spotted enjoying the fine weather as experts say July is set to be even hotter and could break last year's 40.3C record.

title: Taylor Swift 'snubbed personal invite from Meghan to appear on her Spotify podcast'
description: Taylor Swift 'was asked by Meghan herself to appear on Archetypes but her representative declined'. The blow comes as Netflix and Spotify have said they were 'underwhelmed' by the couple's lack of ideas.

title: Twin sisters who give birth hours apart on the same day - and even at the same hospital!
description: Twin sisters Sarah Brown and Claire Harkin (pictured) were stunned to deliver their babies hours apart on the same day and at the same hospital, in what must be a million-to-one chance.

title: Vineyard cuts alcohol in most popular range to dodge higher duty
description: Producers are looking to cut the amount of alcohol in their wine - down from 12.5 to 11 per cent - to reduce the duty charged and to ensure their products remain affordable.

title: Now Chinese spy cams are found outside MI6 HQ
description: Cameras made by Hikvision - which is banned in US federal buildings on national security grounds - have been installed on a lamp post across the road from MI6 headquarters.

title: Partygate accuser Sir Bernard Jenkin is a coward, say Boris allies
description: Sir Bernard Jenkin was blasted by Boris Johnson loyalists for refusing to come clean over his alleged participation in a 'birthday drinks' bash for his wife Anne, a Tory peer, on December 8, 2020.

title: Chelsea's neighbours score victory against plans to use its stadium for all-day music events
description: Residents living close to the Stamford Bridge ground in Fulham, West London, banded together to raise objections following an article about the proposal in The Mail on Sunday in November.

title: Anti-terror law in wake of Manchester Arena bomb are a threat to thousands of village halls
description: Concerns have been raised over proposed new rules to improve security in public places by volunteer-run centres, including the village hall in Kingsclere, Hampshire (pictured).
